y guiding stars, my light in these dark times.', 15666, 0), (74411, 'My mom says . . . there are bad people who hurt others for fun . . . and there are good people who do it by accident. Like, they make a mistake? I think you''re a good person.', 11598, 0), (74412, 'Penelope? Thank you. For not leaving me alone to deal with this . . . when things got hard. other people would have. You''re a true friend.', 11598, 0), (74413, 'Ambition had a price, and that price was friendship.', 958, 0), (74414, 'The most important things are the hardest things to say, because words diminish them...', 578, 0), (74415, 'He had insinuated himself into Nina''s life in a gentle, measured way, through small gifts and intelligent, respectful notes. His attention was never overbearing, nor disturbingly selfless, but wise and reserved.', 15667, 0), (74416, 'Here’s my usual party strategy: find the liquor, find the food, find the space where two walls meet. Alienate enough people around you to have some breathing room. Find the attractive people—this shouldn’t take long; they’ll be the ones getting everything they want in life. Once you’ve found them, stare hungrily at them all evening, and interpret every alarmed flicker of eye contact from them as a new stage in your relationship.', 15668, 0), (74417, 'I don''t want to leave.', 11598, 0), (74418, 'She knew me beyond my actionsBeyond my shallow attempts at happiness.She knew I had darknessAnd when I undressedAnd showed her what I was made ofShe noddedKnowing I was unrepairableAnd said ''I''ll be here for you anyway', 12107, 0), (74419, 'I shrug and shuffle my toe across the carpet in front of me, feeling silly. "So? It''s a compliment being like you."  All the humor evaporates from his face and his honey-brown eyes. Within seconds he has me in his arms and he hugs me like I''m the most important thing in the world to him. "Don''t ever change, Callie Lawrence," he whispers in my hair. "Promise me you won''t.', 655, 0), (74420, 'I wish I had 