ll-being.', 15693, 0), (74514, 'Friends with whom you seriously fall out are death. Sometimes it will be completely your fault that this happens, and the shame and sadness of the parting will stay close for a long time.', 15693, 0), (74515, 'You don’t hit on your best friend’s love interest', 15694, 0), (74516, 'The eyes of his friend were moist and dark, and in them he saw the little rectangled pictures of himself that he had watched a thousand times.', 934, 0), (74517, 'My father and he had cemented (the verb is excessive) one of those English friendships which begin by avoiding intimacies and eventually eliminate speech altogether. They used to exchange books and periodicals; they would beat one another at chess, without saying a word.', 284, 0), (74518, 'Friendship provides the ideas, tools, comfort, and motivation that nothing else can give or offer.', 5089, 0), (74519, 'All the luxuries you name I have, still the peace I do not get.One day, my friend called me off, and I get the world to which I belong.', 15695, 0), (74520, 'Go and have another look at the roses. And you will understand that yours is indeed unique in all the world.', 69, 0), (74521, 'Where there is love, there are plenty of things that rhyme.', 5089, 0), (74522, 'When you''re alone, you harbour one hundred percent of all the good things. But this also means that you harbour all the bad things. I learnt my own goals slowed down when I was with others, but having shared the good things, sharing the pain, having that friendship excelled what I alone couldn''t do. It doesn''t need to be logical, friendships are a part of life, and when is that logical? Life doesn''t make sense, but you don''t have to live it alone.', 5113, 0), (74523, 'When you''re alone, you harbour one hundred percent all of the good things. But this also means that you harbour all the bad things. I learnt my own goals slowed down when I was with others, but having shared the good things, sharing the pain, having that friendship excelled what I alone couldn''t do. It doesn''t need to be logical, friendships are a part of life, and when is that logical? Life doesn''t make sense, but you don''t have to live it alone.', 5113, 0), (74524, 'You hear so many people talk about finding their soul mates only in relation to who they marry, but I think that, as women, our real soul mates are often found when we recognize some version of ourselves in someone else.', 15674, 0), (74525, 'Sometimes you can look back on times in your life and know that God was guiding you even when you didn''t know you were supposed to be listening.', 15674, 0), (74526, 'Pull something out and show me.” I said thoughtlessly. Isaac started snickering, Ethan joined in. Asher was holding back a laugh, his cheeks turning pink. I thought about what I said and started laughing. There are just some things you can’t say in a room full of guys.', 15696, 0), (74527, 'The coolest thing about fandom is the friendships made along the way with people who share your passions.', 15697, 0), (74528, 'As an adult, most of my friends are women . . . they, too, had that moment when they realized they were all the “other girls,” and that every girl in the world is, too.', 12633, 0), (74529, 'London is yours. If you want it.', 15697, 0), (74530, 'Rachelle choked on a laugh. “You were always stronger.”“You,” said Amélie, “were always foolish enough to think that mattered.', 481, 0), (74531, 'Eyes speak louder than words; life is precious; hate is poison; God is the best of all possible friends; silence and time are valuable treasures; happiness can be just as powerful in pretend; and soft licorice is a temptation in any color, especially exotic black.', 1456, 0), (74532, 'We have fangirl shorthand.', 15697, 0), (74533, 'Looking back on months and years of intimacy, to feel that your friend, while you still remember the moving words you exchanged, is yet growing distant and living in a world apart—all this is sadder far than partings brought by d